      <hedline>
        <hl1>Boom Box</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Maureen Ogle letter on Michael Lewis's August 13 article notes today's VCR's can skip through commecials (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>In 1985, VCR's were difficult to program, but today's machines can be operated by anyone who can read. And they have this nifty ''fast forward'' button (which, on many models, becomes faster forward when pushed twice) that enables the user to -- ta dah! -- skip the commercials.</p>
        <p>Maureen Ogle  Ames, Iowa</p>
      </block>
